The Southern Oasis Casualty Ledger network requires recovery of administrative satchels abandoned in the Manifest Shade Court district when the last adjudicator rotation collapsed. Each recovered satchel contains burn ledger entries that cannot be reconstructed from secondary sources. Locate one intact registrar's satchel in the administrative district and return it so the casualty record can be completed.
The registrar's heatproof satchel has been recovered and its burn ledger contents confirmed intact. The Southern Oasis Casualty Ledger network has incorporated the recovered entries, closing a gap in the administrative record that predates the current adjudicator cycle. A formal recovery confirmation has been transmitted to the Ration Dispute Court for archive purposes.

